table asyncio_extra126.asyncio_queue_put_nowait_task_done_varnames:
  description: "asyncio.Queue.put_nowait, task_done, and get_nowait __code__.co_varnames checks in asyncioqueuecv126 namespace — wave 255 theme: asyncio.Queue.put_nowait.__code__.co_varnames.__getitem__(0).__eq__('self')==True; asyncio.Queue.put_nowait.__code__.co_varnames.__getitem__(1).__eq__('item')==True (put_nowait is 'def put_nowait(self, item)', non-coroutine, raises QueueFull immediately if full); asyncio.Queue.put_nowait.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2 (only self and item; no local waiting variables since put_nowait does not wait); asyncio.Queue.task_done.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==1 (task_done is 'def task_done(self)' with only self; the shortest co_varnames list in this spec with just 1 entry vs put's 3, get's 2, put_nowait's 2); asyncio.Queue.get_nowait.__code__.co_varnames.__getitem__(0).__eq__('self')==True (get_nowait is non-coroutine: 'def get_nowait(self)', raises QueueEmpty immediately if empty); asyncio.Queue.get_nowait.__code__.co_argcount.__eq__(1)==True (single positional param: self); asyncio.Queue.get_nowait.__code__.co_varnames.__len__()==2 (self plus local item that stores the retrieved value); contrasting put vs put_nowait: put has 3 co_varnames (extra local putter) while put_nowait has only 2 (no waiting logic); verified with Python 3.14.3"
